 # Biome safe autofix broke signal parser while loop — investigate guardrails
 
-
+A biome safe autofix (--write, NOT --unsafe) restructured a `while ((x = expr) !== -1)` loop into separate init + while + reassign-at-bottom. A `continue` statement in the loop body bypassed the reassignment, causing an infinite loop on inputs with consecutive newlines.
+
+This suggests that even 'safe' biome autofixes can introduce runtime bugs when they restructure control flow containing `continue` or `break` statements.
+
+**Action items:**
+- Investigate whether biome has a rule or option to flag restructured loops with continue/break
+- Consider adding a post-fix test run to our workflow (run tests immediately after any `bun check --write`)
+- Document this pattern in the AGENTS.md as a known risk
+
